#' census at column `tick` â€” not the working column `tick+1` that this interval's step
#' kernel and transmission build â€” its result does NOT depend on where the step kernel
#' runs. That lets every model use ONE ordering: `carry_forward â†’ step â†’ calc_foi â†’
#' transmission`, with `calc_foi` placed immediately before `transmission`. Under it an
#' agent contributes to the FOI on exactly the `D` census columns it occupies (it enters
#' `I` at column `entry+1` via either the step kernel's Eâ†’I or transmission's Sâ†’I, and
#' recovers `D` columns later), so the realized basic reproduction number is the full
#' `R0 = beta * D` â€” for both direct Sâ†’I (SIR) and SEIR-style entry, with no `beta*(D-1)`
#' artifact and no per-family special-casing.
